[update 09082015]
DownloadArtifacts.py usage:
python ci/DownloadArtifacts.py -j "757-767-Avionics" -l linux-clang mac windows -t TEST --login login --password passOrAPIToken
where:
-j is job name in the jenkins
-l list of labels for downloading from
-t target path (abs or relative to script working directory)
also, you can put the "access" file (a file with login and pass or API Token) and specify it through --access_file key (abs or relative to script working directory).
Default value for --access_file key is "access".


[initially]
Continue integration settings.
We are using Jenkins as a CI system with following settings of the build item.
steps:
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
# debug

1. Build shell command: "export -p" - Printing all set environments variable for current session.

2. Build shell command: "python ci/test.py cleanup" - Cleans previous test artefacts if there are existing. 

3. Build shell command: "python ci/configure.py cleanup" - Cleans previous configuration artefacts if there are existing. 
3. Build shell command: "python ci/configure.py debug --test --prefix ${SOME_ENV_PATH} --sts" - Configures project.

4. Build shell command: "python ci/build.py cleanup" - Cleans previous build artefacts if there are existing. 
4. Build shell command: "python ci/build.py debug" - Runs build.

5. Build shell command: "python ci/test.py debug" - Runs tests

6. Build shell command: "python ci/install.py debug" - Runs installing.

# release

7. Build shell command: "python ci/configure.py cleanup" - Cleans previous configuration artefacts if there are existing. 
7. Build shell command: "python ci/configure.py release --test --prefix ${SOME_ENV_PATH} --sts" - Configures project.

8. Build shell command: "python ci/build.py cleanup" - Cleans previous build artefacts if there are existing. 
8. Build shell command: "python ci/build.py release" - Runs build.

9. Build shell command: "python ci/test.py release" - Runs tests

10. Build shell command: "python ci/install.py release" - Runs installing.

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#

11. Post build: "Publish JUnit test result report" parameters is  "test_reports/*.xml" - Analysing tests result.

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
